Pod auto-scaling and scale-down settings depend on Kubernetes configurations: Kubernetes has a feature called Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) that scales pods based on demand. Scale-down times vary, but common configurations include: 5 to 15 minutes of inactivity before a pod is deleted. Some systems use a longer timeout (e.g., 30 minutes to 1 hour) for expensive workloads.
